Response ID: resp_3645
Response Text: 1. Offering housing, or housing stipends, rent subsidy. Significant compensation with no restrictions (or as minimal as possible) so that artists can afford to live and buy food and pour into their friends and family. Going to Black, Brown and lifelong Austinites as a priority. 2. rolling deadlines with quick responses (so artists can move quickly and arent waiting) 3. insurance or health care for artists who struggle with mental health and part-time jobs. Maybe caseworkers. 4. Connecting artists with donors and customers. But not turning them loose. A program to help coordinate this interaction to be sure the artist is supported. So the donors dont screw them or try to sue them or something. Most artists do not have legal resources to navigate contracts or in case they need extra time or something.

